3A%20AI%20can%20boost%20workers%2C%20not%20just%20replace%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20President%20Brad%20Smith%20has%20a%20message%20for%20tech%20leaders%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-graduates-ai-backlash-commencement-speeches-anxiety-job-market-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecollege%20graduates%20booed%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20this%20year's%20commencement%20speeches%3A%20listen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20post%20published%20Wednesday%2C%20Smith%20said%20recent%20pushback%20%E2%80%94%20including%20from%20students%20about%20to%20enter%20the%20job%20market%20%E2%80%94%20against%20AI's%20role%20in%20society%20should%20serve%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20powerful%20wake-up%20call%20for%20the%20tech%20sector.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20those%20in%20the%20tech%20sector%20who%20seemingly%20want%20to%20pursue%20a%20future%20where%20computers%20replace%20jobs%2C%20and%20AI%20becomes%20more%20capable%20than%20people%2C%20the%20next%20generation%20has%20offered%20a%20compelling%20response%3A%20'Not%20so%20fast%2C'%26quot%3B%20Smith%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20executives%20have%20cast%20AI%20as%20transformative%20and%2C%20at%20times%2C%20warned%20that%20its%20impact%20on%20jobs%20could%20be%20brutal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-warning-ai-could-eliminate-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDario%20Amodei%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20last%20year%20that%20AI%20is%20becoming%20so%20powerful%20that%20it%20could%20wipe%20out%20half%20of%20all%20entry-level%20jobs.%20Microsoft%20AI%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-ceo-mustafa-suleyman-white-collar-tasks-automation-prediction-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMustafa%20Suleyman%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20in%20February%20that%20computer%20work%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20fully%20automated%20by%20an%20AI%20within%20the%20next%2012%20to%2018%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it's%20perhaps%20unsurprising%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecollege%20graduates%20%E2%80%94%20who%20typically%20fill%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emany%20of%20the%20entry-level%20office%20jobs%20Amodei%20said%20will%20no%20longer%20exist%20%E2%80%94%20have%20booed%20executives%20like%20former%20Google%20CEO%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudents-boo-eric-schmidt-google-ceo-ai-university-arizona-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEric%20Schmidt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20painted%20AI's%20impact%20in%20rosy%20terms%20during%20their%20graduation%20speeches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20blog%20post%2C%20Smith%20acknowledged%20the%20students'%20concerns.%20He%20said%20today's%20graduates%20face%20%26quot%3BAI%20automation%20of%20tasks%20in%20current%20entry-level%20positions%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20pressure%2C%20especially%20in%20tech%2C%20from%20companies%20that%20are%20reducing%20head%20count%20while%20pouring%20billions%20into%20AI%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20leaders%20have%20begun%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-openai-doomer-boomer-pivot-ai-jobs-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echange%20their%20tone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20emphasizing%20productivity%20gains%20rather%20than%20job%20losses.%20Multiple%20leaders%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-companies-embracing-ai-are-hiring-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Palantir%20CEO%20Alex%20Karp%2C%20who%20have%20also%20warned%20about%20AI%20displacing%20jobs%2C%20are%20now%20emphasizing%20how%20it%20can%20help%20employees%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ework%20more%20efficiently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sunnier%20messaging%20comes%20as%20AI%20companies%20eye%20public-market%20debuts%20and%20face%20serious%20local%20opposition%20to%20the%20data%20centers%20needed%20to%20power%20their%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20has%20not%20been%20a%20leading%20voice%20in%20the%20AI%20jobs-doom%20chorus.%20His%20post%2C%20however%2C%20echoed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20more%20optimistic%20refrain%20now%20coming%20from%20Silicon%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20often%20is%20at%20its%20best%20when%20we%20use%20it%20to%20strengthen%20existing%20human%20capabilities%20and%20endeavors%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIn%20short%2C%20people%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20make%20themselves%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Smith%20argued%20that%20the%20AI%20panic%20may%20be%20getting%20ahead%20of%20reality.%20He%20said%20AI%20is%20likely%20to%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20general-purpose%20technologies%20of%20the%20next%2025%20years%2C%20but%20warned%20that%20tech%20leaders%20often%20overestimate%20how%20quickly%20new%20tools%20will%20transform%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20they%20frequently%20overestimate%20the%20arrival%20of%20new%20technology%2C%20especially%20the%20pace%20of%20its%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20even%20more%20importantly%2C%20they%20underestimate%20the%20capabilities%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-backlash-gen-z-microsoft-president-brad-smith-graduation-speeches-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781169241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a29789359f798e5451f595e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-backlash-gen-z-microsoft-president-brad-smith-graduation-speeches-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Microsoft%20President%20Brad%20Smith%20says%20tech%20leaders%20should%20listen%20to%20the%20booing%20crowds%20at%20college%20graduation%20ceremonies.%22%2C%22author%2